A U.K. high court ordered the state
to return 679,000 pounds ($1 million) to billionaire South
African Christo Wiese three years after the cash was initially
seized from him at a London airport,  Business Day  reported,
citing Wiese.  The cash, found in his luggage, was confiscated in April
2009, the Johannesburg-based newspaper reported.  To contact the reporter on this story: 
